The paper focuses on speeding up convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The methods presented in the paper involve exploiting redundancy in filters, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of CPU and GPU frameworks, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS).
